article.description: North Dakota State rolls over Viterbo 93-49
article.headline: North Dakota State rolls over Viterbo 93-49
article.linkText: North Dakota State rolls over Viterbo 93-49
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Mike Felt was 8 of 13 from the floor, nailing 7 of 11 three pointers, to score 23 points and lead North Dakota State to an easy 93-49 victory over Viterbo Friday. The whole North Dakota team was hot as the Bison hit 58% of their shots in the first half and 35 of 66 shots for the game. Kary Brown hit a iump shot to open the scoring for North Dakota State, but Viterbo came back to take the lead 9-8 on a Cole Lewis jumper with 13:53 remaining in the first half. Felt scored less than a minute later to put the Bison out front 13-11. They never looked back as they opened up a 43-16 lead at the half. Taylor Braun had 16 points and 5 rebounds for North Dakota State. Cole Lewis led Viterbo with 12 points.
